instruction:
Modern JavaScript has shorthand for common patterns:

- `x ||= value` — set x to value only if x is falsy
- `x &&= value` — set x to value only if x is truthy  
- `x ??= value` — set x to value only if x is null/undefined

These replace verbose guard patterns:
```js
// Before: settings.theme = settings.theme || 'dark';
// After:  settings.theme ||= 'dark';
```
